            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.16396/2606.16396v1/figs/hero.jpg",
                "caption": "Figure 1:SP3. We introduce a Plug-and-Play image restoration algorithm(left)that iteratively projects degraded observations onto a tightly structured latent space using a Spherical Encoder (SE) generative prior. The trajectory along the sphere illustrates our gradient-free, alternating optimization approach, which navigates the image manifold to enforce data consistency. The magnified crops highlight the algorithm’s “anytime” generation capability, demonstrating how it stably converges to produce perceptually sharp and plausible details from the very first iteration.(right)SP3achieves perceptual quality comparable to state-of-the-art zero-shot methods, while being3−630×3-630\\timesfaster.",
                "position": 262
            },
            {
